    "Thus, in the context of this article, we define a catalogue of semantic artefacts as a dedicated web-based system that fosters the availability, discoverability and long-term preservation and maintenance of semantic artefacts.",
    "Two years ago, moved by the principles highlighted in the EOSC IF report, the EOSC Association (https://www.eosc.eu) promoted the creation of thirteen second-generation task forces (EOSC TFs, https://eosc.eu/eosc-task-forces), comprising selected experts from the members of the association, to create guidelines and tools to allow the development and deployment of the EOSC.",
    "These TFs have been grouped into four macro topics:",
    "• Metadata and data quality -focussed on providing guidelines and tools for the discoverability, understanding, and reusability of research objects, and aiming at developing models and benchmarks to assess the data FAIRness and quality;",
